"categories":["Array","Binary Indexed Tree","Ordered Set"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Hard","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"There are some red and blue tiles arranged circularly. You are given an array of integers `colors` and a 2D integers array `queries`.\n\nThe color of tile `i` is represented by `colors[i]`:\n\n- `colors[i] == 0` means that tile `i` is **red**.\n\n- `colors[i] == 1` means that tile `i` is **blue**.\n\nAn **alternating** group is a contiguous subset of tiles in the circle with **alternating** colors (each tile in the group except the first and last one has a different color from its **adjacent** tiles in the group).\n\nYou have to process queries of two types:\n\n- `queries[i] = [1, sizei]`, determine the count of **alternating** groups with size `sizei`.\n\n- `queries[i] = [2, indexi, colori]`, change `colors[indexi]` to `colori`.\n\nReturn an array `answer` containing the results of the queries of the first type *in order*.\n\n**Note** that since `colors` represents a **circle**, the **first** and the **last** tiles are considered to be next to each other.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n**Input:** colors = [0,1,1,0,1], queries = [[2,1,0],[1,4]]\n\n**Output:** [2]\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/3245-alternating-groups-iii/3245-screenshot-from-2024-06-03-20-14-44.png]]\n\n**\n\nFirst query:\n\nChange `colors[1]` to 0.\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/3245-alternating-groups-iii/3245-screenshot-from-2024-06-03-20-20-25.png]]\n\nSecond query:\n\nCount of the alternating groups with size 4:\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/3245-alternating-groups-iii/3245-screenshot-from-2024-06-03-20-25-02-2.png]]\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/3245-alternating-groups-iii/3245-screenshot-from-2024-06-03-20-24-12.png]]\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n**Input:** colors = [0,0,1,0,1,1], queries = [[1,3],[2,3,0],[1,5]]\n\n**Output:** [2,0]\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/3245-alternating-groups-iii/3245-screenshot-from-2024-06-03-20-35-50.png]]\n\nFirst query:\n\nCount of the alternating groups with size 3:\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/3245-alternating-groups-iii/3245-screenshot-from-2024-06-03-20-37-13.png]]\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/3245-alternating-groups-iii/3245-screenshot-from-2024-06-03-20-36-40.png]]\n\nSecond query: `colors` will not change.\n\nThird query: There is no alternating group with size 5.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `4 <= colors.length <= 5 * 10⁴`\n\n- `0 <= colors[i] <= 1`\n\n- `1 <= queries.length <= 5 * 10⁴`\n\n- `queries[i][0] == 1` or `queries[i][0] == 2`\n\n- For all `i` that:\n\n- `queries[i][0] == 1`: `queries[i].length == 2`, `3 <= queries[i][1] <= colors.length - 1`\n\n- `queries[i][0] == 2`: `queries[i].length == 3`, `0 <= queries[i][1] <= colors.length - 1`, `0 <= queries[i][2] <= 1`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/alternating-groups-iii/","problemName":"Alternating Groups III","problemNumber":3245,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"There are some red and blue tiles arranged circularly. You are given an array of integers `colors` and a 2D integers array `queries`.\n\nThe color of tile `i` is represented by `colors[i]`:\n\n- `colors[i] == 0` means that tile `i` is **red**.\n\n- `colors[i] == 1` means that tile `i` is **blue**.\n\nAn **alternating** group is a contiguous subset of tiles in the circle with **alternating** colors (each tile in the group except the first and last one has a different color from its **adjacent** tiles in the group).\n\nYou have to process queries of two types:\n\n- `queries[i] = [1, sizei]`, determine the count of **alternating** groups with size `sizei`.\n\n- `queries[i] = [2, indexi, colori]`, change `colors[indexi]` to `colori`.\n\nReturn an array `answer` containing the results of the queries of the first type *in order*.\n\n*